node.text:
IF YOU GOT VALUE FROM THIS POST TYPE “VALUE” and I’ll drop more. 

Even if you no longer use an old credit card, it's typically best to keep the account open. That's because your credit scores benefit from a long credit history and a high total credit limit. Closing established accounts will shorten the average age of your accounts and lower your total credit limit. It will take years before an account closed in good standing drops off your credit report, but the effects on your credit utilization rate are immediate. If a credit card comes with a high annual fee you can't afford, closing the account could be a good option—or ask your issuer to downgrade the card to a no-fee version if possible.

node.text:
When my dad could no longer provide for my mom and I… when my grandpa passed away… or when I got beat up in school.
.
It felt like there was no way out. It felt like I had hit a level below rock bottom.
.
Looking back at my whole life, there are many moments I don’t want to go back to.
.
However, it was through those tough moments I started reading and exploring. I started businesses to make money. And I found mentors who trained me.
.
So when it feels like you’ve hit rock bottom, and it feels like there’s no hope or help to get from anywhere…
.
There’s only one way out...
.
And that is through it.
.
Let me ask you…
.
Looking back at your life, haven’t you had those moments that you wish never happened, aren’t those also great moments that changed something within you?
.
Maybe you lost a girlfriend or boyfriend, and you found someone better.
.
Maybe you got fired from your job and started your own thing.
.
Or maybe you lost a friend or relative, and now you appreciate the people around you more.
.
So whatever you’re going through right now, just know that even the worst storm will stop. And how can you learn from it?
.
I believe you can do this. Give me a “I can do it” in the comments below if you can do it.

You might think rich people are rich because they make a lot of money… 

And there's definitely a lot of truth to that. 

But rich people stay rich and build their wealth not just because of the money they make. 

They become richer because of their habits. 

They don’t have the habits of poor people who spend 95% of their income and only invest 5% or less. 

Instead, they minimize the money they spend on wants and invest a large part of their income each year. 

How can you change your spending habits this year to begin investing more?

node.text:
Most people tell you to get a safe job.

That having a safe job is the best way to have job security.

Well, let me ask you.

Do you think you could easily be replaced in your job?

If you quit, wouldn't someone fill your spot in a few weeks?

If you're that replaceable, do you think there is really such thing as "job security?"

Exactly.

So don't rely on your job to give you a good income.

Rely on your skills.

Develop a high-income skill that can make you more than $10K a month.

And rely on YOURSELF to make you money.

Not anyone else.

Comment below if this makes sense.

If you are ready to develop your high-income skills, DM me.
